keyValuePair.Value: You've claimed a famous Double. What's next for the club?

There's more to come.

Winning both these competitions is a great achievement, for sure. But I don't want anybody resting on their laurels. The team's flying at the moment. Let's kick on from here now. I hope this Double can be the start of a golden era for the club.
The boys have been brilliant.

It's been an incredible campaign. The players have been magnificent and this Double is a reward for all their efforts. I believe they're capable of even more. It's a very exciting time for everybody connected with the club.
The lads have earned this success.

Winning one trophy's special. To win two is a measure of just how hard these players have been willing to work for each other and for the club. They deserve all the glory. And they probably deserve a little rest now, too!
%1s Double Up!

It's an historic achievement for the club. With %4s leading the way, %1s have pulled off a magnificent domestic double, winning both the %2s and the %3s. Congratulations are in order all round at the end of this hugely successful campaign.

It's an historic achievement for the club, winning both the %1s and the %2s in a single season. It's a unique Double. The question fans are already asking, though, is how can the team follow this? What are your plans going forward?
We're just getting started!

The thing that sets this team apart is that they're never satisfied. Of course we're happy and we'll celebrate doing this amazing Double. But I can tell you the players are already hungry for more. They want these two trophies to be just the first of many!
This is a special team.

It's been a pleasure watching this team develop over the past few months. They've worked so hard, individually and collectively. I think lifting these two great trophies is a reward for their commitment and a recognition for their quality. I'm absolutely delighted for them and for the fans.
It's not always been easy.

There have been times during this campaign where people doubted these players. They've had some difficult spells, that's for sure. But they're brave and they've got a great spirit between them. Those are the qualities which have made this amazing Double possible.
This Double is a great achievement. What's been the secret of your success?

We hope this is the start of something special.

The lads have worked so hard and deserve all their success. I want to challenge them, though. We've developed a winning mentality in our dressing room. I want that to push us on now to win more trophies in future
I couldn't have asked for more.

It's been an absolute privilege working with this group of players. It's as if they've taken ownership of the dressing room. I pick the team but then they go out and deliver, game after game. I know I can trust them. This Double is down to their spirit and commitment.
It's been worth the hard work.

We've got some very talented players, of course. But the secret behind winning this Double isn't a secret at all. It's been all about hard work. Even in difficult games, they've believed in themselves and each other. They've been willing to put their bodies on the line in every single game.
Did you always think this Double was within your grasp?

I'm not sure anybody would have forecast such a dramatic end to the season. You'd already won the %1s and now you've lifted the %2s to complete a unique Double. Were you always sure your boys had an achievement like this in them?
It's about desire.

It's been great. I think the lads have learnt so much about themselves on the way to this Double. They've found a hunger and a desire that's made it easy for me to manage them. I want them to go out and do it all over again now. Let's not just settle for this!
It's a team with spirit, isn't it?

I knew we had a good enough group of players to compete. What I didn't know was whether they'd be strong enough mentally to go on and actually win trophies. I think pulling off this Double speaks for itself, doesn't it? They've been fantastic, a credit to the club.
The harder you work, the luckier you get.

This group of players have really been prepared to suffer. They deserve all this success. We've had lucky breaks in some games maybe, but the boys have earned everything that's come to them. A great work ethic can take a team a very long way, can't it?
An unprecedented Treble. Can you believe it?
Suddenly you're looking down on the world from the top of a very tall mountain. This Treble is an incredible achievement. How have the team managed to find the consistency to pull it off?
Winning is a good habit.

We really have just gone from game to game. And we've given everything each time to get the result. It's almost like the Treble has snuck up on us. Our focus was always on the next hurdle. But here we are. I hope the boys can build on it. We've got the winning habit now.
They've gone into the history books.

This is a great club with a marvellous history but this is something else again, isn't it? A Treble? Nobody will ever forget what the boys have achieved here. They deserve to be thought of as real heroes from now on.
They've given everything.

I don't think I've ever worked with a group of players who've been so committed to the cause, so willing to go out and give everything for each other. Definitely, I've never managed a team that's pulled off a Treble like this. Hard work's got its reward here, that's for sure.
A clean sweep! How's this Treble been possible?

It's a remarkable achievement, completely dominating domestic competition this season, winning the %1s, the %2s and now the %3s. How has the team been able to maintain this incredible consistency? And at such a high level?
This team motivates itself!

Winning is great, of course. But what's even better, from a manager's point of view, is that it inspires your players. Once the boys had won one trophy, they were desperate to win the next and the next. That desire has been the secret behind this Treble. I hope it's only the start for this team.

It's all down to their hunger.

A unique Treble. Could you possibly have foreseen that achievement?

I hope there's more to come from this team.

Good players and a great attitude. It's as simple as that. But the very best sides never pause for breath. This should be all the motivation the boys need to go on and win more trophies in future. At this club, we mustn't ever settle for less.
We've looked unbeatable.

This team has proved it deserves to be ranked up there with the very best. We've played some great football along the way, but trophies are what you're remembered by. Winning a Treble means these lads deserve to take their place in the history books at this club.
You couldn't ask for more from your players.

This team has been developing for a while now. Every training session, every game, they've given me everything. I couldn't have asked for more in terms of commitment and sacrifice. It's been a pleasure working with them. This Treble is the reward they deserve.

It felt like history being made as you added the %4s to the three trophies you'd already won. It's an absolutely incredible achievement for your team. What has set them apart from the rest this campaign?
Now we have to do it again!

Every trophy you win, the challenge is to go on and win it again. The boys have pulled off this amazing Quadruple and deserve all the compliments coming their way. The challenge, though, is to ask ourselves: we're the best, but can we go out and prove it all over again next time around?
They've proved they're the best around.

I think, over the course of the campaign, the team just forgot how to lose. To seal a Quadruple is something very special indeed. The quality of football, the desire, the self-belief: I think these players are maybe the best in the history of the game.
They've sacrificed everything for the team.

We knew we were good enough to lift trophies. But to go on and win all four is an unbelievable achievement. They've given everything. For me, for the club and for each other. They deserve this success. They've given us their absolute maximum in each and every game.
A unique Quadruple. How do you build on this success?

Your team has dominated domestic football and claimed a Europa League title as well to complete an historic quadruple. The supporters have never witnessed a campaign like it. How do you rate the achievement? And is there more to come?
Everybody will be coming for us now!

We've had a fantastic season and this Quadruple sets the seal on it. Incredible! But you can be sure everyone will be desperate to knock us off our perch now. That can be our motivation. We'll have to go out and prove ourselves now all over again.
Those boys are winners!

I don't know where the lads found those reserves of determination and self-belief, to be honest. I knew they were good enough. But to produce that level of performance over and over again? Incredible! No-one can say this Quadruple isn't deserved.
They've been unbelievably professional.

Lots of teams play well now and again. Sometimes that's enough to win them a trophy. Just think for a minute about what this group of players has achieved. A Quadruple like this is unprecedented and it's the reward they deserve for giving it everything, game after game.
